        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated based on literature (Schmidt, J.H., 2007, Life cycle assessment for rapeseed oil and palm oil; Omni Tech International, 2010, Life Cycle Impact of Soybean Production and Soy Industrial Products), (Vionnet, S., Quantis Water Database - Technical Report, 2012). The process starts when rapeseeds enter the oil plant. It includes the processes: raw material reception and storage, screening, pre-heating, rolling, conditioning, pressing, clarification, drying, solvent extraction, heating, centrifugation, drying, etc. The process ends when refined rapeseed oil leaves the plant. It is assumed that 80% of water use is allocated to cooling water and 20% of water is allocated as process water. The evaporation rate for process water used is the same as in case of oil production from soybeans.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="1.1913755202128454E-05" mu="-11.337816926045551" variance="0.01" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.052700000000000004"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="4" temporalCorrelation="5" geographicalCorrelation="3" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="1"/>
        </uncertainty>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">oxidane</synonym>
